"title": "1654: numbers, 11–99",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1654",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Significant numbers include twelve, often associated with the full number of God's people, and multiples of ten, especially forty and seventy.</p>\n<h2>Eleven</h2>\n<h3>Eleven sons of Jacob</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:22\">GEN 32:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:9\">GEN 37:9</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's eleven disciples</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:16\">MAT 28:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:14\">MRK 16:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:9\">LUK 24:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:33\">LUK 24:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:26\">ACT 1:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:14\">ACT 2:14</a></p>\n<h2>Twelve</h2>\n<h3>Twelve tribes of Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:28\">GEN 49:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:22-Gen35:26\">GEN 35:22–35:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:4\">EXO 24:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:21\">EXO 28:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod39:14\">EXO 39:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:29\">JDG 19:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra8:35\">EZR 8:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:7\">ACT 26:7</a></p>\n<h3>Representatives of the twelve tribes</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:23\">DEU 1:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:12\">JOS 3:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh4:2-Josh4:3\">JOS 4:2–4:3</a></p>\n<h3>The church symbolised as twelve tribes</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:1\">JAS 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:4-Rev7:8\">REV 7:4–7:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:12\">REV 21:12</a></p>\n<h3>Twelve apostles</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:14\">MRK 3:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:1-Matt10:4\">MAT 10:1–10:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:28\">MAT 19:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:1\">LUK 9:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:30\">LUK 22:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:70-John6:71\">JHN 6:70–6:71</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:2\">ACT 6:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:5\">1CO 15:5</a> <em>The term “the Twelve” is used here even though only eleven disciples remained at the time referred to.</em></p>\n<h2>Fourteen</h2>\n<h3>Passover on the fourteenth day of the first month</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:16\">NUM 28:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod12:6\">EXO 12:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:5\">LEV 23:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:2-Num9:5\">NUM 9:2–9:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh5:10\">JOS 5:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:1\">2CH 35:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:19\">EZR 6:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:21\">EZK 45:21</a></p>\n<h3>Passover on the fourteenth day of the second month</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num9:10-Num9:11\">NUM 9:10–9:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:2-2Chr30:3\">2CH 30:2–30:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:15\">2CH 30:15</a></p>\n<h3>Periods of fourteen years</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:41\">GEN 31:41</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:2\">2CO 12:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:1\">GAL 2:1</a></p>\n<h3>Genealogy of Jesus Christ in spans of fourteen generations</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:17\">MAT 1:17</a></p>\n<h2>Fifteen</h2>\n<h3>Festivals on the fifteenth day</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:6\">LEV 23:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:34\">LEV 23:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:39\">LEV 23:39</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:17\">NUM 28:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num29:12\">NUM 29:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:32-1Kgs12:33\">1KI 12:32–12:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek45:25\">EZK 45:25</a></p>\n<h2>Twenty</h2>\n<h3>Twenty as the minimum age in a census</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod30:14\">EXO 30:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod38:26\">EXO 38:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:3\">NUM 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:18\">NUM 1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:29\">NUM 14:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:2\">NUM 26:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:23\">1CH 27:23</a></p>\n<h3>Twenty as the minimum age for Levitical service</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:24\">1CH 23:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:27\">1CH 23:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:17\">2CH 31:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra3:8\">EZR 3:8</a></p>\n<h2>Thirty</h2>\n<h3>Thirty as the age for beginning a life's work</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:23\">LUK 3:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:46\">GEN 41:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:1\">1SA 13:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:4\">2SA 5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:1\">EZK 1:1</a> <em>The “thirtieth year” may refer to Ezekiel's age.</em></p>\n<h3>Thirty as the minimum age for Levitical service</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:3\">NUM 4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:23\">NUM 4:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:30\">NUM 4:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num4:47\">NUM 4:47</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:3\">1CH 23:3</a></p>\n<h3>The Thirty in David's army</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:23\">2SA 23:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:25\">1CH 11:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:24\">2SA 23:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:15-1Chr11:42\">1CH 11:15–11:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:4\">1CH 12:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:18\">1CH 12:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:6\">1CH 27:6</a></p>\n<h3>Thirty pieces of silver</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:15\">MAT 26:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech11:12-Zech11:13\">ZEC 11:12–11:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:3\">MAT 27:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:9\">MAT 27:9</a></p>\n<h2>Forty</h2>\n<h3>Forty days</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:4\">JON 3:4</a></strong> <em>Forty days is a standard period, sometimes viewed as a time of preparation or testing before a major event.</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:4\">GEN 7:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:12\">GEN 7:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:17\">GEN 7:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:6\">GEN 8:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:18\">EXO 24:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:28\">EXO 34:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:9\">DEU 9:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:18\">DEU 9:18</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:1-Matt4:2\">MAT 4:1–4:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:13\">MRK 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:1-Luke4:2\">LUK 4:1–4:2</a> <em>Jesus Christ fasted for forty days in the wilderness.</em>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:25\">NUM 13:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:16\">1SA 17:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:8\">1KI 19:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:3\">ACT 1:3</a></p>\n<h3>Forty years as a general term for a generation</h3>\n<p>God's anger against Israel in the wilderness:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:34\">NUM 14:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:13\">NUM 32:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh5:6\">JOS 5:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:10\">PSA 95:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:9\">HEB 3:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:17\">HEB 3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:35\">EXO 16:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut2:7\">DEU 2:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:2-Deut8:4\">DEU 8:2–8:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:5\">DEU 29:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:21\">NEH 9:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos2:10\">AMO 2:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:36\">ACT 7:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:18\">ACT 13:18</a></p>\n<h3>Other significant forty-year periods</h3>\n<p>Forty-year periods in Moses' life:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:7\">EXO 7:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:7\">DEU 34:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:23\">ACT 7:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:30\">ACT 7:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:36\">ACT 7:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg3:11\">JDG 3:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:31\">JDG 5:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg8:28\">JDG 8:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam4:18\">1SA 4:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:4\">2SA 5:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs2:11\">1KI 2:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:27\">1CH 29:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:42\">1KI 11:42</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:30\">2CH 9:30</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs12:1\">2KI 12:1</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr24:1\">2CH 24:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:21\">ACT 13:21</a></p>\n<h2>Fifty</h2>\n<h3>The fiftieth year as the Year of Jubilee</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:10-Lev25:11\">LEV 25:10–25:11</a></strong> <em>The word “jubilee” refers to the liberation of slaves, rather than to a fixed period of time. The number 50 represents the year following seven periods of seven years, i.e., 49 years + 1.</em></p>\n<h2>Seventy</h2>\n<h3>Seventy people went down to Egypt</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:27\">GEN 46:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:5\">EXO 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>Seventy years of God's judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:11-Jer25:12\">JER 25:11–25:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:21\">2CH 36:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa23:15-Isa23:17\">ISA 23:15–23:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer29:10\">JER 29:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:2\">DAN 9:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech1:12\">ZEC 1:12</a></p>\n<h3>Seventy years as the human lifespan</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:10\">PSA 90:10</a></p>\n<h3>Groups of seventy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod24:1\">EXO 24:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:16\">NUM 11:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:24-Num11:25\">NUM 11:24–11:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:2\">JDG 9:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:1\">LUK 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:17\">LUK 10:17</a></p>\n<h3>Seventy as a large number</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:22\">MAT 18:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan9:24\">DAN 9:24</a></p>",
